    Novel therapies are challenging the standards of drug development. Agents
  with specific biologic targets, unknown dose-efficacy curves, and limited
  toxicity mandate novel designs to identify biologically optimal doses. We
  review two model-based designs that utilize either a proportional odds model
  or a continuation ratio model to identify an optimal dose of a single or
  two-agent combination in a Phase I setting utilizing both toxicity and
