  training group. Among patients with a proportion score of at least 50{\%} in
  the validation group, the response rate was 45.2{\%}. Among all the patients
  with a proportion score of at least 50{\%}, median progression-free survival
  was 6.3 months; median overall survival was not reached. CONCLUSIONS
  Pembrolizumab had an acceptable side-effect profile and showed antitumor
  activity in patients with advanced non-small-cell lung cancer. PD-L1
  expression in at least 50{\%} of tumor cells correlated with improved
